text.section:
Except as otherwise provided by KRS Chapters 605 and 635, an order of commitment or an order of supervision or probation made by the court in the case of a child may be terminated at any time prior to expiration on the court's own initiative or on motion by:
A child who is affected by an order of juvenile session of District Court;
The family, custodian, guardian, or legal representative of such a child;
The Department of Juvenile Justice or the cabinet;
The county attorney of the county in which the committing court presides; or
Any other person having an interest in the welfare of the child.
